v 3
d googlechart. Stata wrapper for the Google Charts (Visualization API)
d library, with Texas 2036 brand defaults.
d
d googlechart is a sibling -- not a replacement -- to sparkta2.  Both
d produce self-contained interactive HTML from Stata; they target
d different use cases.  sparkta2 embeds d3 + topojson inline and works
d offline (briefs, embargoed reports, sub-state Texas geography).
d googlechart loads google.charts/loader.js from gstatic.com (required
d by Google's Terms of Service -- the loader cannot be self-hosted) and
d in return gives 14 chart types, native filter dropdowns (Dashboard +
d ControlWrapper), polished default tooltips, an interactive Table type
d with free-text search, and animation on most chart types.
d
d Supported chart types (v0.1):
d   column, bar, line, area, combo, pie, donut, scatter, bubble,
d   geo (country + US-state level), timeline, table (searchable),
d   histogram, divbar (Pew-style diverging stacked bar).
d
d Requires: Stata 17+, network access at view time for the resulting
d HTML, sparkta2 helpers (sparkta2_appendfile.ado, sparkta2_embedjs.ado)
d for embedding the engine into the output HTML.
d
